===Etymology 2===
From {{inh|sh|sla-pro|*a||and, but}}, from {{etyl|ine-bsl-pro|sh}} {{m|ine-bsl-pro|*ō}}.

====Conjunction====
{{sh-conjunction|c|a}}

# [[but]], [[and]] (compare {{m|sh|sc=Cyrl|а̏ли}})
#: {{ux|sh|учио сам ц(иј)ело посл(иј)еподне, а ништа нисам научио|t=I studied for the whole afternoon, but I didn't learn anything|inline=1}}
#: {{ux|sh|а како бисте ви то направили?|t=and how would you do that?|inline=1}}
# [[while]] (on the contrary), [[whereas]]
#: {{ux|sh|столови су црвени, а столице су зелене|t=the tables are red, whereas the chairs are green|inline=1}}
# {{label|sh|with {{m|sh|sc=Cyrl|да}} {{m|sh|sc=Cyrl|не}}}} [[without]] (usually after negative verbs)
#: {{ux|sh|не могу се укључити у расправу, а да не направим неред|t=I cannot enter a discussion without making a mess|inline=1}}
#: {{ux|sh|одлази, а да није рекао ни збогом|t=he's leaving without even saying goodbye|inline=1}}
# ({{m|sh|sc=Cyrl||а}} {{m|sh|sc=Cyrl|и̏па̄к}}) [[and]] [[yet]]
#: {{ux|sh|прави пријатељ зна све о теби, а ипак те воли|t=the real friend knows everything about you, and yet he loves you|inline=1}}
# ({{m|sh|sc=Cyrl||а}} {{m|sh|sc=Cyrl|ка̏моли}}) not to mention, [[let alone]]
#: {{ux|sh|у мору лоших в(иј)ести тешко је остати објективан, а камоли оптимистичан|t=in the sea of bad news it's hard to stay objective, let alone optimistic|inline=1}}
# ({{m|sh|sc=Cyrl||а}} + {{m|sh|sc=Cyrl|и}} + {{m|sh|sc=Cyrl|да}}) [[even if]]
#: {{ux|sh|а и да јесам то направио, не би то учинило неку разлику|t=even if I did it, it wouldn't have made much of a difference|inline=1}}
# ({{m|sh|sc=Cyrl||а}} + {{m|sh|sc=Cyrl|и}}) and [[so]], and [[also]], and [[too]]
#: {{ux|sh|свиђају ми се плавуше, а и ја се покојој свидим|t=I like blondes, and some of them even like me|inline=1}}
#: {{ux|sh|били су жалосни, а и ја сам|t=they were sad, and so am I|inline=1}}

===Etymology 3===
Attested since the 15th century. Probably of onomatopoeic origin. Compare Slovene {{m|sl|a}}, Russian {{m|ru|а}}, Lithuanian {{m|lt|õ}}, Latin {{m|la|ō}} and Ancient Greek {{m|grc|ὦ}}. These could all derive from Proto-Indo-European interjection {{m|ine-pro||ō|oh, ah}}, but each form in individual languages could easily be an independent, expressive formation.

====Interjection====
{{sh-interjection|c|a}}

# [[oh]], [[ah]]
#: {{ux|sh|а да?|t=oh really?|inline=1}}

